As a user, I want to be able to view the animals in a clean, concise grid format.
As a contractor who is taking on the project after the original developers are done with it, I want to see a UML diagram, so that I can understand how the data is being mapped out.

As a contractor who is taking on the project after the original developers are done with it, I want to see their unit tests they wrote, so I can get a good idea of what inputs should be expected, and what outputs should be expected.

As a contractor who is taking on the project after the original developers are done with it, I want to see a list of data sources that the original developers used, so that I can see whether they still fit my current needs
As a developer who is calling the RESTful APIs that the original developers built, I want to see documentation for these RESTful APIs, so that I may understand how to  use their API

As a contractor who is taking on the project after the original developers are done with it, I want to see a technical report, so that I can understand how the developers planned out the structure of their application
As a user, I want to know more about the team who is behind the website so that I can either give suggestions or share my comments on the site.
As a user, I want to be able to scroll through and search in the database to see which which animals are on the verge of extinction
As a user, I want to know about the threats that one type of animals face, so that I can help preventing the threats if that is something within my ability.
As a user, I want to know the countries of where the endangered animals live so that I can have a better understanding the relation between the environment, human interaction and the animals.
As a user, I want to know about the habitats so that I can learn which animals belong to which habitats and how many types of animals can share the habitat together.

As a user, I want to know 3 aspects for each endangered animal: the habitats it resides in, the countries it resides in, and the threats that it faces, so that I can gain an overall understanding of the particular animal's predicament.
As a user, I want to be able to see an image of an animal, so that I have an understanding of what the endangered animal is.
As a user, I want to be able to see a video of an animal, so that I have an understanding of how the endangered animal operates.
As a user, I want to be able to get all the threats of an animal, so that I have an understanding of how the endangered animal is threatened.
As a user, I want to be able to get all the habitats and countries of an animal, so that I have an understanding of where the animal resides.
As a user, I want to be able to see an image of a habitat, so that I have an understanding of what the habitat is and what type of animals could live there.
As a user, I want to know if whether a threat is ongoing or not, so that I have an general understanding of how dangerous the threat is to the animals it is affecting.
As a user, I want to be able to see an average severity score of a threat (from 1-10), so that I have an understanding of how dangerous the threat is to the animals it is affecting.
As a user, I want to be able to open on google maps and see where a country is, so that I can have a good understanding of the geographical place of the country, relative to the world.
As a developer using the RESTful API, I want to be able to be able to pull all the data for all animals at once, so that I can obtain the data for all affected animals.
As a user, I want to be able to view the animals in a clean, concise grid format.
As a user, I want to be able to sort the attributes by in descending order by clicking on the column header of each of them.
As a user, I want to be able to sort the attributes by in ascending order by clicking on the column header of each of them.
As a user, I want to be able to restrict the number of instances displayed on a page so that I won't have to wait to long for the site to load.
As a user, I want to be able to search for countries by keywords so that I don't have to find them manually by looking at all the instances.
As a user, I want to be able to search for threats by keywords so that I don't have to find them manually by looking at all the instances.
As a user, I want to be able to search for habitats by keywords so that I don't have to find them manually by looking at all the instances.
As a user, I want to be able to search for animals by keywords so that I don't have to find them manually by looking at all the instances.
As a user, I want to be able to see the endangered animals for the countries that I type in the filter box so that I don't have to click through each individual country model.
As a developer using the RESTful API, I want to be able to be able to pull all the data for all threats at once, so that I can obtain the data for all the threats that affect the animals.
